eNCA’s Nobesuthu Hejana reports. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - An estimated R10-million was spent by Western Cape disaster management to extinguish 75 fires over December and January. Authorities say while the amount was accounted for in just seven days, causes ranged from accidental to deliberate fires. READ: Komani Town Hall in Eastern Cape goes up in flames However, disaster management in the province says that it's still financially prepared should fires break out in the next two months. eNCA’s Nobesuthu Hejana reports in the video above.